FBIS4-45426 "jptdd026__l94012" JPRS-TDD-94-026-L JPRS Narcotics 7 June 1994 LATIN AMERICA BRAZIL Colombian Cartels' `Most Important Man' in Country Eludes Colombian Cartels' `Most Important Man' in Country Eludes Police PY0706142894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 7 Jun 94 PY0706142894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Portuguese BFN [Text] Antonio Mota Graca, aka Curica, who was responsible for the transportation of the seven metric tons of cocaine seized in Tocantins State, is the most important man from the Colombian cartels in Brazil. Although 13 drug traffickers have been arrested, Curica again escaped Federal Police. In 1991, he was freed from inside a Military Police patrol car when he was leaving jail to testify before the court in Itapecirica da Serra, Sao Paulo State.
